<TITLE> Robbers arrested in Patuakhali </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Patuakhali, Apr 19 (bdnews24.com)  Police on Sunday arrested eight robbers from different places of Patuakhali. Police also seized a revolver and five bottles of Phensidyl from the town's gymnastics field. Police did not make any arrests. Moniruzzaman, Patuakhali Sadr police station's sub-inspector told bdnews24.com that a special team of police was able to arrest the robbers on the basis of good intelligence. He said that eight robbers who were arrested were Palash Khandakar Montu, Yousuf Hayder, Harun Hayder, Motalib Akand, Rob Hawlader, Riaz Chowkider, Abdus Sattar Mridha and Harrrun Hawlader. There had been many robbery cases filed against them at Sadr thana police station, he said. On the same night the police also recovered stolen cows from Sheakhati area of the town. Police arrested a man named Saiful, 24, while his three associates managed to flee. bdnews
